Micon</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urhad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhad</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:47:27 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This is actually pretty nice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Not requiring the skin at all would probably be a bug and fixed (like the shaman quest).  However, if one skin can be used to complete multiple staff turn ins, this would justify the previous claim of 2-4 weeks time.  In this instance, under perfect conditions, a skin would be used just before another was dropped, and all wizards with the staves at that time would be able to do the turn in.  This would reduce the limiting factor to the VS drop, which appears to be about 1 drop in 2-4 weeks since the patch.  The mistletoe powder drops insanely commonly.  It looks like about a 50% drop rate (I could just be lucky, but I never have been before).  The phinigel staff, even if pretty rare is still more common than the VS staff based solely on spawn time.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Granted, people aren't a trusting bunch, and until it's posted with a log somewhere that this method works, people will be wary that other wizards will steal their arantir turn-in.  Still, you should trust the members of your guild at least, and it should require only 1 skin per guild (provided you get the skin last, or save it til the end).  However... the wizards without the skin will definately need to pump their faction up.  I think there's a thread somewhere on here about doing that.  If all else fails you can always pay 1000 pp per loop and give potions to camin (or just give 1000pp stacks to camin if that gives faction).  So there's your uber guild part - go sell a orc hatchet for 200,000 pp (if a website says it, it must be true!) and you should be all set!<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It would be nicer to get some first hand info about the turn in (does arantir despawn after you turn in the first 3 staves?  When you hail him, do you get a faction change like the efreeti in sol temple? What kind of con is arantir before and after the note hand in if you do the quest as it's supposed to be done?), but that doesn't seem to be happening.  Perhaps someone will read this and check it out - and possibly save their friends a few months camp time in the PoF :P<br>
<br>
Rhad<br>
